text.__SUMMARY__:
Acacia masliniana, commonly known as Maslin's wattle is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Plurinerves. It is native to an area in the Mid West and Goldfields-Esperance regions of Western Australia.The rounded shrub typically grows to a height of 1 to 3 metres (3 to 10 ft). It blooms from July to September and produces yellow flowers.
The shrub is named for the botanist Bruce Maslin.
